  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: It is possible to rewrite chats history if user changes date settings of his device (e.g. changes current date to yesterday). Then, the other user who receives messages shows them in the middle of the chat. By this, it's very easy for a malicious user to break public chat history. It is also an issue from security point of view.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nIncoming messages are shown in correct order.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUser who changed datetime of his device can inject new messages in the middle of a chat history.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Create 1-1 chat between 2 devices\r\n- Send some messages from each device\r\n- Device A: go to the device settings and change date to yesterday. Then send a message\r\n- Device B: sees the message was sent yesterday \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.25\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
